SPONSOR UNIT – NO BOARD APPROVAL -

RENOVATION HAS BEGUN!

BE PART OF THE PROCESS!

Introducing apartment 19C at 185 West End Ave! This 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom apartment with a dining alcove is set to undergo a complete renovation. Situated on a high floor with serene western views. This spacious unit has a 26-foot terrace offering stunning vistas of the city skyline and the Hudson River.

The upcoming renovations will feature a modern kitchen with new white cabinetry, elegant marble backsplash, and countertops. The kitchen will be equipped with high-end appliances, including a Sub Zero refrigerator, Wolfe stove, wine cooler and Bosch dishwasher. Both bathrooms will be renovated with all new fixtures including marble floors and subway tiled walls. Additionally, the entire apartment will have new engineered hardwood floors, adding a touch of contemporary elegance to the space. Washer/dryers are not allowed.

The maintenance fee covers utilities.

There is a monthly capital assessment of $142.39.

Please note that the photos are renderings and virtually staged pictures will be provided shortly.

Located at 185 WEA, this full-service coop apartment offers an unbeatable location just steps away from Lincoln Center, Columbus Circle, and Riverside/Central Parks. Residents will also have access to the private 5-acre Lincoln Towers Park, complete with a playground, gardens, and recreational courts/fields, all managed by the Lincoln Towers Community Association. The coop employs a dedicated full-time staff, including 24-hour door attendants, concierge and a live-in superintendent, ensuring a high level of service and security.

Amenities at 185 WEA include an in-house dry cleaning service, a members’ gym, a package room, a playroom, parking, and a private driveway.

FRONT PARKING SPOT AVAILABLE AT ADDITIONAL COST.
